EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to business; requiring the governing body of a
county and incorporated city to take certain actions
relating to the establishment of a regional business
license; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a board of county commissioners of a county or
2 governing body of a city to regulate all character of lawful trades, callings,
3 industries, occupations, professions and business conducted within its county or
4 city, as applicable. (NRS 244.335, 266.355, 268.095) Existing law also requires
5 certain boards of county commissioners and governing bodies of a city to enter into
6 an agreement to establish a multijurisdictional business license for certain
7 contractors. (NRS 244.33501, 268.0951) Sections 1 and 2 of this bill require each
8 board of county commissioners and each governing body of an incorporated city to
9 adopt a model ordinance for the establishment of a regional business license and
10 sets forth certain requirements for such a model ordinance, including requiring the
11 model ordinance to establish: (1) the proposed boundaries of the region in which
12 the regional business license is valid; and (2) proposed categories of businesses for
13 which a regional business license will be issued.
14 Sections 1 and 2 also require each board of county commissioners and each
15 governing body of an incorporated city to: (1) cooperate with each other board of
16 county commissioners and governing body of an incorporated city in the proposed
17 region to determine whether the boards and governing bodies should enter into an
18 agreement to establish such a regional business license for any specified category
19 of business; and (2) consider certain factors relating to the similarity of any existing
20 county or city requirements for such businesses when determining whether to enter
21 into such an agreement. Lastly, sections 1 and 2 require that, if the board of county
22 commissioners and governing body of an incorporated city determine to enter into
23 an agreement to establish a regional business license, each board and governing
24 body shall: (1) establish by ordinance a system for issuing the regional business
