1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Each board of county commissioners shall adopt a model
4 ordinance for the establishment of a regional business license
5 within the region, which must, without limitation:
6 (a) Establish the boundaries of the proposed region and each
7 incorporated city that is located within the boundaries of the
8 proposed region;
9 (b) Establish a system for issuing a regional business license
10 for categories of businesses set forth in the model ordinance to
11 engage in such business within the boundaries of the proposed
12 region;
13 (c) Include the requirements for obtaining the regional
14 business license;
15 (d) Include the fees for the issuance and renewal of the
16 regional business license; and
17 (e) Include any other requirement necessary to establish the
18 system for issuing the regional business license.
19 2. Each board of county commissioners shall cooperate with
20 each other board of county commissioners and governing body of
21 each incorporated city in the region proposed in the model
22 ordinance adopted pursuant to subsection 1 or section 2 of this
23 act, as applicable, to determine whether the boards of county
24 commissioners and governing bodies, as applicable, should enter
25 into an agreement in accordance with the provisions of NRS
26 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, to establish a regional business
27 license for any specified category of business in accordance with
28 the model ordinance adopted pursuant to subsection 1 or section 2
29 of this act, as applicable.
30 3. In determining whether to enter into an agreement
31 pursuant to subsection 2 to establish a regional business license
32 for a specified category of business, the board of county
33 commissioners and governing bodies, as applicable, shall consider
34 whether the existing requirements of the county or incorporated
35 city for any business that falls within the proposed category:
36 (a) Provide for the same or substantially similar fees for an
37 application for or an application to renew the existing license for
